{
  "texts": [
    "CNNs are computationally intensive during the training phase, primarily owing to the convolution operations.",
    "However, they benefit from the parallel processing capabilities of modern GPUs, which can offset their computational demands significantly.",
    "In the CNN-LSTM architecture, the output of the CNN layers served as the input to the LSTM layers.",
    "Hence, both the CNN and LSTM equations presented above are utilized.",
    "Combining CNNs and LSTMs increases the computational costs of both architectures."
  ]
}